Configuration (.cfg) File Format

****This format should be strictly followed***

/********************************************************
/*DEBUGMODE=
/*PORT=
/*HOSTNAME=
/*********************************************************

-Make sure absolute path of the configuration file is given in the program
-Make sure there are not any whitespaces following the values entered
-Make sure configuration file doesnt start with an empty line
-Order of 'DEBUGMODE' , 'PORT' , 'HOSTNAME' should not changed or touched

-DEBUGMODE=1 to run porgram in debug mode
-DEBUGMODE=0 to run porgram wihtout debug mode

-Make sure you have provided absolute path in java program in Property Class
-Advisable to run server from home directory(For testing purpose it is fine if the program is not run from home directory)



